      "content": "The idea of removing yourself to bring peace to him is a tragic misunderstanding of love; you are the very foundation of his world, not a weight holding it down. No amount of quiet passing truly frees a child from the grief of losing their mother, and only a foundation of care can prevent such devastating isolation later. It is far better to ask for concrete help with your daily routine than to imagine a world without the warmth you provide, because leaving him alone is the last legacy you ever want to leave behind.",
